29:
Forgive me, Alk! Wake up! Please
don't die on me!
34: The hell are you two doing?
41:
Well, just answer me one thing. Why
did you two decide to start running
drills out of nowhere?
43:
Normally you're content enough to
fight training dummies alone. You're
all, "die this!" and "murder that!"
47: Hm. I do NOT say stuff like that.
63:
Fine, I guess I should change my
battle taunts. It looks like I need even
MORE training.
67:
That's not at all what I meant... Why
were you punching the stuffing out
of Alk anyway?
71:
I needed to learn how to instruct
others.
75:
You wanted to learn how to teach
those two assassin children, right?
79:
Are you sure you should be up and
moving right now?
82:
Maybe not. It feels like an elephant is
sitting on my head.
86:
Wait, we have assassin children in
our care? Or do you mean those two
kids that Barrek placed in hiding?
89:
Yeah, those runts. He said he'd go
meet 'em when the time is right. So I
guess he's thinking sooner rather
than later?
96:
Honestly... He's already been visiting
them on occasion.
119: So, yeah, he's been a bit too strict.
122:
"Too fragile?!" Maybe you should
hold back a bit, huh?!
130:
But if you don't put your entire soul
into your strike, how will your
opponent know you're being serious?
132:
When I was in my youth, I was utterly
defeated by a single blow. It
destroyed my ego.
136: Right, and what happened after that?
139:
For three days and nights, I was on
the verge of death.
150:
Perhaps you should take a less
physical route?
153:
Putting these children in harm's way
seems counterproductive. At least
you wouldn't risk bodily harm from a
lecture.
165:
Lower your stance a bit, Alk. There.
Good form.
167:
Stella, your movements look more
coordinated already. Keep it up.
169:
Maybe try going a little... Ah, never
mind. You're doing great.
173:
I thought you would be a terrible
instructor, but I'm glad to be wrong.
179:
By vocalizing my techniques, I'm
gaining a better understanding of
my own capability.
181:
Thank you. It feels as though I've
discovered a new way to increase
my skill.
185: Always the stoic one, aren't you?
188:
Besides, I benefit from both Alk and
Stella becoming better fighters.
191:
There's an opponent that I must
face one day. And when I do, it will
be best if we're all prepared.
194:
Whoever could it be? I can't imagine
Alk or Stella getting wrapped up in
your affairs.
198: It's you, Light. The mythical hero.
201:
Your eyes speak of your true
strength, the depth of your combat
experience. You must be stronger
than me. Or am I wrong?
204:
Your martial arts are beyond regular
human levels. YOU must be the
better fighter.
207:
But ONLY in terms of martial arts. Do
you think a few skilled punches
would be enough to take you down?
211:
Probably not. My power comes from
a divine source. It would be like
pitting a house cat against a wolf.
214:
That's exactly the kind of challenge I
crave. I won't ever get stronger
resting on my laurels.
217:
Promise me, Light, that once you've
finished your quest, you'll duel me
the very next evening!
220:
I take it back. You're not stoic; you're
downright crazy!
222:
But, very well. You have my word.
After I have bested the Lord of
Shadow, I will defeat you next.
227:
Hahahaha! Alk! It's sparring time!
Ready your blade! Here I come!
